09/03/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The Parliamentary committee dealing with constitutional issues adopted on Thursday (March 8th) the draft version of Montenegro's new constitution and numerous alternatives.
The parliament is expected to discuss the draft on March 26th, after which it will be placed up for public debate.
According to the procedure for adopting a new constitution, the parliamentary committee must adopt the final proposal after the public debate.
If it is not adopted with a 2/3 majority in Parliament, a referendum will be held, where more than 50% of those that vote need to support it.
Montenegro, which became an independent country in 2006, must adopt a new constitution in order to become a member of the Council of Europe.
(Vijesti - 09/03/07)
